messages.message: Hey team, I am unable to login to dogfood for past ~1 hour… Whenever i login via https://dogfood.instabase.com/account/login, it redirects back to platform website.
can you once try it in incognito?
@Shubham Oli Thanks!! It works fine in incognito! Will clear cache in normal window and retry… btw do we know why does this happen? I now remember similar thing happening few weeks back as well…
No sure why this happens. Maybe frontend team can help here.

This did not work for me after i cleared dogfood.instabase.com (http://dogfood.instabase.com) cookies but it worked for me after i cleared instabase.com (http://instabase.com) cookies.
Did we make a recent change in auth frontend (<!subteam^SQC4GLFN2>) or backend (account-tservice @Heymian) in the past few days?
We did not, we don't know why this is suddenly an issue but there is a fix up. See this for more details: https://instabase.slack.com/archives/CLBGA5A7K/p1628779265024600
yeah don’t think this is account-service, nothing changed there. but i also ran into this starting yesterday and just worked around with incognito

I see. Meanwhile so that business team are unblocked —
You can remove cookies like this. Click on cookies and then click remove.
